# Vercel KV (waitlist email storage) — Upstash Redis under the hood.
# The conan-license KV store is connected to this project across all envs, so on
# Vercel these are injected automatically. For LOCAL dev, run `vercel env pull`
# to write them into a gitignored .env. (The conan-license secrets are Sensitive
# and unreadable via CLI — connect the store to the project, don't copy creds.)
#
# Until these are set, /api/waitlist still accepts signups but does NOT store
# them (it logs a warning). Once set, emails persist to the `waitlist:emails` set.
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# Resend — forwards each NEW signup to the team inbox (hello@conan.sh).
# Optional: until RESEND_API_KEY is set, signups still save to KV but no email is
# sent (logged as a warning). RESEND_API_KEY: create at resend.com → API Keys.
# WAITLIST_FROM must be on a Resend-VERIFIED domain (verify conan.sh in Resend).
# WAITLIST_NOTIFY_TO / WAITLIST_FROM are optional overrides for the defaults.
RESEND_API_KEY=
WAITLIST_NOTIFY_TO=hello@conan.sh
WAITLIST_FROM=Conan <noreply@conan.sh>
